## Test Suites (phpunit.xml)

| Suite | Directorio(s) | Cubre |
|-------|---------------|-------|
| **Base** | `tests/Base/` | Clases core en `base/` (fs_model, fs_core_log, fs_functions, etc.) |
| **Security** | `tests/Security/` | Componentes de seguridad (PasswordHasher, CsrfManager) |
| **Traits** | `tests/Traits/` | Traits de Symfony (ValidatorTrait) |
| **Cache** | `tests/Cache/` | Sistema de caché (CacheManager) |
| **Api** | `tests/Api/` | Autenticación y routing REST API |
| **ClientesCore** | `tests/ClientesCore/` | Modelos del plugin core de clientes |

## Convenciones Obligatorias

### Namespace y Autoload

```php
<?php

declare(strict_types=1);

namespace Tests\Base;

use PHPUnit\Framework\TestCase;
use PHPUnit\Framework\Attributes\Test;
use PHPUnit\Framework\Attributes\DataProvider;
use PHPUnit\Framework\Attributes\CoversClass;
```

- Namespace raíz: `Tests\` (PSR-4 via `autoload-dev` en composer.json)
- Clases en `base/` no autoloaded: usar `require_once`

### Atributos PHPUnit 11 (preferidos sobre prefijo test)

```php
#[CoversClass(\fs_model::class)]
class FsModelTest extends TestCase
{
    #[Test]
    public function varStrEscapesCorrectly(): void
    {
        // ...
    }

    #[Test]
    #[DataProvider('provideEmails')]
    public function validatesEmail(string $email, bool $expected): void
    {
        // ...
    }

    public static function provideEmails(): array
    {
        return [
            'valid'   => ['user@example.com', true],
            'invalid' => ['not-an-email', false],
        ];
    }
}
```

## Patrones de Mocking

### fs_model sin DB (anonymous subclass)

```php
$model = new class() extends \fs_model {
    public function __construct() {}
    public function delete() { return false; }
    public function exists() { return false; }
    public function save() { return false; }
};
```

### Query Builder con mock de fs_db2

```php
$mockDb = new class {
    public function escape_string(string $str): string {
        return addslashes($str);
    }
};
$qb = new \fs_query_builder($mockDb);
```

### Resetear estado estático (fs_core_log, etc.)

```php
protected function setUp(): void
{
    parent::setUp();

    $ref = new \ReflectionClass('fs_core_log');
    $prop = $ref->getProperty('data_log');
    $prop->setAccessible(true);
    $prop->setValue(null, null);
}
```

### Resetear Singletons (CacheManager, etc.)

```php
protected function setUp(): void
{
    parent::setUp();
    \FSFramework\Cache\CacheManager::reset();
}
```

## Regla de Oro: Cobertura Mínima

Todo código nuevo en `src/` DEBE tener tests que cubran:

1. **Caso feliz** — el flujo normal funciona
2. **Caso de error** — inputs inválidos, excepciones, edge cases
3. **Valores límite** — null, string vacío, 0, arrays vacíos, máximos

## Ejemplo Completo: Test de Seguridad

```php
<?php

declare(strict_types=1);

namespace Tests\Security;

use FSFramework\Security\PasswordHasherService;
use PHPUnit\Framework\TestCase;
use PHPUnit\Framework\Attributes\Test;

class PasswordHasherServiceTest extends TestCase
{
    private PasswordHasherService $hasher;

    protected function setUp(): void
    {
        $this->hasher = new PasswordHasherService();
    }

    #[Test]
    public function hashIsNotPlaintext(): void
    {
        $plain = 'mi-contraseña-segura';
        $hash  = $this->hasher->hash($plain);

        $this->assertNotEquals($plain, $hash);
    }

    #[Test]
    public function verifyCorrectPassword(): void
    {
        $plain = 'mi-contraseña-segura';
        $hash  = $this->hasher->hash($plain);

        $this->assertTrue($this->hasher->verify($hash, $plain));
    }

    #[Test]
    public function verifyWrongPasswordFails(): void
    {
        $hash = $this->hasher->hash('correcta');

        $this->assertFalse($this->hasher->verify($hash, 'incorrecta'));
    }

    #[Test]
    public function sameInputProducesDifferentHashes(): void
    {
        $plain = 'misma-contraseña';
        $hash1 = $this->hasher->hash($plain);
        $hash2 = $this->hasher->hash($plain);

        $this->assertNotEquals($hash1, $hash2);
        $this->assertTrue($this->hasher->verify($hash1, $plain));
        $this->assertTrue($this->hasher->verify($hash2, $plain));
    }
}
```

## Ejemplo: Test de Validación con Trait

```php
<?php

declare(strict_types=1);

namespace Tests\Traits;

use PHPUnit\Framework\TestCase;
use PHPUnit\Framework\Attributes\Test;
use FSFramework\Traits\ValidatorTrait;
use Symfony\Component\Validator\Constraints as Assert;

class ModeloTest
{
    use ValidatorTrait;

    #[Assert\NotBlank]
    #[Assert\Email]
    public string $email = '';

    #[Assert\NotBlank]
    #[Assert\Length(min: 2)]
    public string $nombre = '';
}

class ValidatorTraitTest extends TestCase
{
    #[Test]
    public function validModelPasses(): void
    {
        $model = new ModeloTest();
        $model->email  = 'test@example.com';
        $model->nombre = 'Juan García';

        $this->assertTrue($model->validate());
    }

    #[Test]
    public function invalidEmailFails(): void
    {
        $model = new ModeloTest();
        $model->email  = 'no-es-un-email';
        $model->nombre = 'Juan';

        $this->assertFalse($model->validate());
    }

    #[Test]
    public function emptyRequiredFieldFails(): void
    {
        $model = new ModeloTest();
        $model->email  = 'test@example.com';
        $model->nombre = '';

        $this->assertFalse($model->validate());
    }
}
```

## Tests para Plugins

Los tests de plugins se ubican en `tests/NombrePlugin/`:

```php
<?php

declare(strict_types=1);

namespace Tests\ClientesCore;

use PHPUnit\Framework\TestCase;
use PHPUnit\Framework\Attributes\Test;

require_once __DIR__ . '/../../plugins/clientes_core/model/core/cliente.php';

#[CoversClass(\cliente::class)]
class ClienteModelTest extends TestCase
{
    #[Test]
    public function testMethodReturnsExpected(): void
    {
        // Usar anonymous subclass si el constructor requiere DB
        // o crear instancia directa si el método es puro
    }
}
```

## Configuración

- **phpunit.xml** en la raíz del proyecto
- **bootstrap**: `tests/bootstrap.php` — define `FS_FOLDER`, `FS_DB_TYPE`, `FS_TMP_NAME`
- **Deprecations**: `SYMFONY_DEPRECATIONS_HELPER=weak` — loguea deprecaciones sin fallar
